gomodel:SYNGO_4751  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1b: \"Cell surface NCAM was labeled by indirect immunofluorescence of formaldehyde-fixed hippocampal neurons maintained in culture for 12 d. Neurons were then permeabilized and labeled with antibodies against synaptophysin and AP-2 or AP-3. Note that NCAM- and synaptophysin-positive clusters colocalize with AP-2 and AP-3 accumulations\"\n\nFigure 1c: \"Hippocampal neurons maintained in culture for 12 d were colabeled with antibodies against synaptophysin, AP-2, and AP-3. Note overlapping accumulations of AP-2 and AP-3, which colocalize with synaptophysin-positive clusters\"\n\nPresynaptic localization is further supported by AP3 involvement in SV endocytosis (Figure 8). The antibody for AP3 targeted AP3B2.. Experimental description: M&M: \"To prepare cultures of hippocampal neurons, 1- to 3-d-old C57BL/6J and NCAM-/- mice of either sex from homozygous breeding pairs were used.\"\n\nantibody:\n\"neuronal adaptin-like protein beta (βNAP) subunit of AP-3 (clone 18, catalog #610892)\"\nnote; this is AP3B2" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2022-08-04" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4751" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

